name: ExtensionExplanationOfBenefit_BenefitBalance
title: Cross-version Extension `R5.ExplanationOfBenefit.benefitBalance` for use in FHIR R4
description: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element `ExplanationOfBenefit.benefitBalance` for use in FHIR R4.
purpose:
This extension is part of the cross-version definitions generated to enable use of the
element `ExplanationOfBenefit.benefitBalance` as defined in FHIR R5
in FHIR R4.

The source element is defined as:
`ExplanationOfBenefit.benefitBalance` 0..* `BackboneElement`

Across FHIR versions, the element set has been mapped as:
*  R5: `ExplanationOfBenefit.benefitBalance` 0..* `BackboneElement`
*  R4B: `ExplanationOfBenefit.benefitBalance` 0..* `BackboneElement`
*  R4: `ExplanationOfBenefit.benefitBalance` 0..* `BackboneElement`

Element `ExplanationOfBenefit.benefitBalance` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `ExplanationOfBenefit.benefitBalance`, but has no comparisons.

binding.description: Benefit categories such as: oral, medical, vision, oral-basic etc.

element.definition: True if the indicated class of service is excluded from the plan, missing or False indicates the product or service is included in the coverage.
element.requirements:
Needed to identify items that are specifically excluded from the coverage. Element `ExplanationOfBenefit.benefitBalance.excluded` is part of an existing definition because parent element `ExplanationOfBenefit.benefitBalance` requires a cross-version extension.
Element `ExplanationOfBenefit.benefitBalance.excluded` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `ExplanationOfBenefit.benefitBalance.excluded`, but has no comparisons.
